leads.lead_text: Flowers with a distinct tubular hypanthium (much longer than lobes); floral leaves with white-felted upper surface, stem leaves green above; leaves entire, but apex often retuse; widespread, usually diffuse, mallee subshrub

Flowers with free, tubular part of hypanthium very short (not or hardly longer than lobes); floral and stem leaves similar; leaves emarginate or 3-toothed at apex; rare twiggy subshrub of Hattah and northern Big Desert areas
